{"id": "1526840228009218179", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "content": "Before we translate and send:\n\nHi, I wanted to share some feedback about problematic, unfair, teams and mechanics of the pvp Traphase mode, in the hope that they could be taken in consideration and possibly revisited for a more balanced and enjoyable experience:\n\n- Ramona : Her 0 cost card that give 3 aritmetica can cause various problems, because she can use her copy card to gain 6 arithmetica, possibly at turn 1\\2, leading to early snowball that can enable plays to kill 1 or more units after the first turns of battle. Her 0 cost could possibly be reduced to +2 arithmetica, or have other changes to mitigate this aspect.\n\n- Kathigu-Ra : A possible X cost card damages rework ( example : after 5 or 6 arithmetica consumed, halve the damages increases for further arithmetica used ). At the current moment, she can stack high amount of arithmetica on the 1 or 2 turn to instantly kill an opponent unit with no possibility of counterplay, especially with Ramona in the team.\n\n- Pollux : Sin marks shouldn't be permanently erasing your max HP, if you really want the max HP decreasing mechanism then at least make it temporary just like Saya and only until it gets dispelled.\n\n- Daff : Her 2 cost, particularly with Ramona copy card, can lead to killing 1 opponent on turn 2 and then continuing to spam the 2 cost, continuously increasing his damage, and filling the deck with them to delay the reshuffle and guarantee to draw them every turn. \n\n- Mulligan : Revert back the changes to it. It was actually a features that gives more skills knowing what to discard to make it last draw depending on who you're fighting.                                                                                                                           Now it's just pure RNG, and you have the possibility to immediately redraw the card you just discarded the following turn, this is particularly taxing in the Draft mode, where the  options to control the match are already lower.", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T06:37:57.677000+00:00", "type": 19, "edited_timestamp": "2026-07-15T06:42:36.462000+00:00", "mentions": ["332573289438380032"], "reply_to": "1526541126868144128"}
